38 Irish general election|1938]]\n| {{Composition bar|9|138|hex={{Labour Party (Ireland)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{decrease}}4\n| {{steady}}3rd\n| 128,945\n| 10.0%\n| style=\"background-color:Pink\" |Opposition <small>(FF)</small>\n| William Norton\n|-\n![[1943 Irish general election|1943]]\n| {{Composition bar|17|138|hex={{Labour Party (Ireland)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{increase}}8\n| {{steady}}3rd\n| 208,812\n| 15.7%\n| style=\"background-color:Pink\" |Opposition <small>(FF minority)</small>\n| William Norton\n|-\n![[1944 Irish general election|1944]]\n| {{Composition bar|8|138|hex={{Labour Party (Ireland)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{decrease}}9\n| {{decrease}}4th\n| 106,767\n| 8.8%\n| style=\"background-color:Pink\" |Opposition <small>(FF)</small>\n| William Norton\n|-\n![[1948 Irish general election|1948]]\n| {{Composition bar|14|147|hex={{Labour Party (Ireland)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{increase}}6\n| {{increase}}3rd\n| 115,073\n| 8.7%\n| style=\"background-color:PaleGreen\" |Coalition <small>(FG\u2013LP\u2013CnP\u2013CnT\u2013NLP)</small>\n| William Norton\n|-\n![[1951 Irish general election|1951]]\n| {{Composition bar|16|147|hex={{Labour Party (Ireland)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{decrease}}3<ref name=Labour>The Labour Party and the [[National Labour Party (Ireland)|National Labour Party]] had reunited since the last election. The figures for the Labour party are compared to the two parties combined totals in the previous election.</ref>\n| {{steady}}3rd\n| 151,828\n| 11.4%\n| style=\"background-color:Pink\" |Opposition <small>(FF minority)</small>\n| William Norton\n|-\n![[1954 Irish general election|1954]]\n| {{Composition bar|19|147|hex={{Labour Party (Ireland)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{increase}}3\n| {{steady}}3rd\n| 161,034\n| 12.1%\n| style=\"background-color:PaleGreen\" |Coalition <small>(FG\u2013LP\u2013CnT)</small>\n| William Norton\n|-\n![[1957 Irish general election|1957]]\n| {{Composition bar|12|147|hex={{Labour Party (Ireland)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{decrease}}7\n| {{steady}}3rd\n| 111,74