{"title_page": "Jorge Calandrelli", "text_new": "[[File:Jorge Calandrelli at DMI Grammy Party, 2014.jpg|thumb|Jorge Calandrelli in 2014]]\n'''Jorge Calandrelli''' is an Argentinian-born composer, arranger and conductor known for his work with [[Arturo Sandoval]], [[Yo-Yo Ma]], [[Elton John]], [[Lady Gaga]] and [[John Legend]]. He has won 4 [[Grammy Award|Grammy Awards]] and has received 27 nominations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.afm47.org/press/michael-giacchino-jorge-calandrelli-to-be-honored-at-golden-score-awards/|title=Michael Giacchino, Jorge Calandrelli to be Honored at Golden Score Awards|last=admin|date=2014-09-16|website=47 Blog {{!}} AFM Local 47|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> He won the [[Latin Grammy Award for Producer of the Year]] and [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Instrumental Album|Best Instrumental Album]] for his work on ''[[A Time for Love (Arturo Sandoval album)|A Time for Love]]'' by [[Arturo Sandoval]] in [[11th Annual Latin Grammy Awards|2010]].<ref name=LatinGrammy2010>{{cite news|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/music_blog/2010/09/latin-grammy-nominees-announced-alejandro-sanz-and-camila-among-top-contenders.html|title=Latin Grammy nominees announced: Alejandro Sanz and Camila among top contenders |work=Los Angeles Times|publisher=Tribune Company|accessdate=January 25, 2011|date=September 29, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.latingrammy.com/es/nominees/search|title=20a Entrega Anual del Latin GRAMMY|website=Latin GRAMMYs|language=es|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> Calandrelli has been nominated twice for an [[Academy Awards|Academy Award]] for his work on [[The Color Purple (film)|The Color Purple]] and [[Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RsAnJ7Zx_qgC&pg=RA5-PA28&lpg=RA5-PA28&dq=jorge+calandrelli+++billboard&source=bl&ots=_92ogFrTue&sig=ACfU3U1UNuIxs5KwZFRORL8rSMucqERYVw&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwil2_Ksz8voAhX-JTQIHad_A44Q6AEwBXoECAsQKQ#v=onepage&q=calandrelli&f=false|title=Billboard|date=2012-01-07|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/artists/jorge-calandrelli|title=Jorge Calandrelli|date=2019-11-19|website=GRAMMY.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> \n\n== Early life and career ==\nWhile Calandrelli's mother was a skilled pianist, both his father and grandfather were medical doctors and expected him to follow their path. At age 4, Calandrelli started playing the piano by ear and took lessons at age 8.\n\nIn his late teens, with both of his parents' support, Calandrelli traveled to Europe to pursue a career in music. He arrived in [[Los Angeles]] in 1968 and collaborated with composer and arranger [[Clare Fischer]]. Inspired by him, Calandrelli decided to go back to Argentina and continue honing his skills.\n\nHe would later return to the United States with recommendation letters from the record labels we had worked with in Argentina. Soon, he recorded Russian-American conductor [[Andre Kostelanetz]] and a 65-piece orchestra at [[CBS]]' studio in [[New York City|New York]].<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite book|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RsAnJ7Zx_qgC&pg=RA5-PA28&lpg=RA5-PA28&dq=jorge+calandrelli+++billboard&source=bl&ots=_92ogFrTue&sig=ACfU3U1UNuIxs5KwZFRORL8rSMucqERYVw&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwil2_Ksz8voAhX-JTQIHad_A44Q6AEwBXoECAsQKQ#v=onepage&q=calandrelli&f=false|title=Billboard|date=2012-01-07|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref>\n\nCalandrelli soon started arranging for different artists, achieving wider recognition in [[23rd Annual Grammy Awards|1981]] with first [[Grammy Award]] nomination for [[Grammy Award for Best Arrangement, Instrumental or A Cappella|Best Instrumental Arrangement]] for his work on \"Forget the Woman\" by [[Eddie Daniels]]. In 1987, he was nominated three times at the [[29th Annual Grammy Awards|29th Grammy Awards]]: in the [[Grammy Award for Best Arrangement, Instrumental or A Cappella|Best Arrangement on an Instrumental]] category for \"Solfeggietto/Metamorphosis\" by Eddie Daniels and \"The First Letter\" from [[The Color Purple (film)|The Color Purple]] soundtrack and in the [[Grammy Award for Best Arrangement, Instrumental and Vocals|Best Instrumental Arrangement Accompanying Vocals]] category for [[Tony Bennett|Tony Bennett's]] version of Daniels' \"Forget The Woman \".<ref name=\":4\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.awardsandshows.com/features/grammy-awards-1987-235.html|title=Grammy Award Nominees 1987 - Grammy Award Winners 1987|website=www.awardsandshows.com|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n\nCalandrelli's work with Bennett includes twelve recorded albums, six Grammy Nominations and two Grammy Awards won.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/jorge-calandrelli-mn0000987684/credits|title=Jorge Calandrelli {{!}} Credits|website=AllMusic|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> Bennett's 2011 album \"[[Duets II (Tony Bennett album)|Duets II]]\", arranged and conducted by Calandrelli debuted at No. 1 on the [[Billboard 200]], Jazz Albums and Traditional Jazz Albums charts. This same No. 1 debut was achieved by Bennett's 2014 collaborative album with [[Lady Gaga]] \"[[Cheek to Cheek (album)|Cheek To Cheek]]\", also arranged and orchestrated by Calandrelli.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rivergrandrapids.com/must-see-tv-with-tony-bennet-lady-gaga-cheek-to-cheek-live/|title=Must See TV With Tony Bennet & Lady Gaga: Cheek To Cheek LIVE!|last=Andy Rent|website=100.5 The River|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n\nCalandrelli produced, played the piano, composed, arranged and conducted [[Pl\u00e1cido Domingo|Pl\u00e1cido Domingo's]] 2008 album \"Amore Infinito\", based on lyrics by [[Pope John Paul II]]. The album contains duets by [[Josh Groban]], [[Katherine Jenkins]], [[Andrea Bocelli]], [[Vanessa Williams]] and Pl\u00e1cido Domingo Jr.<ref name=\":5\" />\n\n== Awards ==\n\n=== Golden Score Awards ===\nThe [[American Society of Music Arrangers and Composers|American Society of Music Arrangers and Composers (ASMAC)]] honored Calandrelli with the 2014 Golden Score Award for Arranging.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://parabuenosaires.com/la-legislatura-portena-distingue-al-maestro-jorge-calandrelli/|title=La Legislatura porte\u00f1a distingue al maestro Jorge Calandrelli|last=Aires|first=Parabuenosaires com {{!}} Noticias de Buenos|language=es|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.clarin.com/espectaculos/musica/jorge-calandrelli-pague-derecho-piso-unidos_0_Hkzn6QqZl.html|title=Jorge Calandrelli: \"Nunca pagu\u00e9 derecho de piso en los Estados Unidos\"|last=Clar\u00edn.com|website=www.clarin.com|language=es|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> \n\n=== [[Academy Awards]] ===\nCalandrelli has been nominated twice for the Academy Award for his work on [[The Color Purple (film)|The Color Purple]], directed by [[Steven Spielberg]], and [[Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon]], directed by [[Ang Lee]].<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":3\" />\n\n=== [[Latin Grammy Award|Latin Grammy Awards]] ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Artist\n!Category\n!Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[11th Annual Latin Grammy Awards|2010]]\n|[[A Time for Love (Arturo Sandoval album)|A Time for Love]]\n|[[Arturo Sandoval]]\n|[[Latin Grammy Award for Best Instrumental Album|Best Instrumental Album]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n| -\n| -\n|[[Latin Grammy Award for Producer of the Year|Producer of the Year]]\n|{{Won}}\n|}\n<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n=== [[Grammy Award|Grammy Awards]] ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Artist\n!Category\n!Result\n|-\n|[[23rd Annual Grammy Awards|1981]]\n|Forget The Woman\n|[[Eddie Daniels]]\n|[[Grammy Award for Best Arrangement, Instrumental or A Cappella|Best Instrumental Arrangement]]\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[29th Annual Grammy 